Because it doesn’t have to be EITHER OR. it can always be BOTH AND. 

Here’s why I like to:

LIFT WEIGHTS 💪🏽 🏋🏽‍♀️ 2-3x a week
- for overall health and longevity (strength training really is KING here as we start to age) 
-  to become unbreakable (aka really strong) 
- increased levels of capability and confidence 
- to build a strong body inside and out 
- because I enjoy it 

PRACTICE YOGA 🧘‍♀️ 😌 3-4x a week 
- it helps me process what I’m feeling 
- it gives me space to check in with myself 
- it reminds me to breathe (better) 
- it helps me get unstuck 
- it challenges me mentally 
- it forces me inward 
- because I enjoy it 

TAKE CLASSES 🎀 🤩 1x a week sporadically 
- holds me accountable 
- helps me try something new 
- trains my body in a different way I might not do myself 
- surrounds me with community 
- helps me make new friends 
- because I enjoy it (mostly)

You don’t improve your life by always doing more. You improve it by doing a lot less of what doesn’t matter.

Here’s to more intentional time in the sun my friends.

Curious about what a Sunday sculpt class with coach B looks like? Here’s what we worked on in January. 

1. Spinal undulation and fluidity 

2. Core control and stability 

3. Transition from single leg mountain into airplane 

4. Single leg deadlift/hinge patterns. Ipsilateral hold vs contralateral hold 

5. A new skill to play with 

6. Juicy feel good yoga 

Marrying functional strength training and yoga has been just the adventure I needed this year. Build a strong body that moves well, feels good, and helps you do life a little easier. Sundays at 1230 at @fahrenheityoga I’ll see you there.

Did you know humming can also calm your nervous system? 

❤️ the vagus nerve is an important part of our parasympathetic nervous system and it helps us relax and recover. Humming stimulates our vagus nerve which can lead to decreased stress hormones and increased relaxation 
❤️ humming improves airflow! Humming slows down our breath and increases the amount of oxygen in our blood leading to more calmness and clarity
❤️ humming can also help to release tension in our physical bodies in areas like our neck, throat and jaw. 

Hum along why don’t you.

Tem presente no final…

Minha primeira conquista com produto digital, o the box atingiu a marca de mais de 100k de faturamento.

Porém, o mais importante aqui não é o faturamento, mas sim a quantidade de pessoas que foram atingidas, assim como startups e empresas que atualemnte estão utilizando meus wireframes que construí com base em mais de 12 anos de experiência no mercado internacional de interfaces.

Para quem não me conhece deve achar que estou me exibindo, mas não é isso que quero mostrar aqui. A ideia é transmitir a vocês a mensagem de que tudo tem um começo, o primeiro passo é de suma importância para quem almeja vencer.

Quem já me conhece das antigas e conhece minha jornada sabe que 100k é um faturamento baixo comparado ao que faturo vendendo serviços e fazendo aquilo que amo fazer.

Para mim o The Box é mais um MVP que deu certo e esse é só o começo, esse ano vou exponenciar meu conhecimento e seguir ajudando mais e mais pessoas a melhorar sua vida com design.

Com base nessa comemoração, estou liberando um desconto de 10% para as primeiras 20 pessoas que me responderem aqui...

Quer aproveitar esse desconto? Comenta “100K” e eu te envio o link promocional.

Parsley Health clinicians use functional medicine to get to the root cause of symptoms in order to find the condition (AKA the cause of your symptoms!) This means taking a holistic approach to care—which can look a little different than conventional medicine.

Root-cause medicine uses tools like stress management, healthy sleep habits, exercise, supplements, and practices like acupuncture or a sauna routine, that help to not just resolve symptoms, but heal the underlying condition for good.

Did you know there’s a small butterfly-shaped gland in the front of your neck? Also known as the thyroid, it plays a key role in hormone regulation. However, over 20 million American adults are affected by thyroid conditions—what are the root causes of this common health issue?

While some people are genetically predispositioned to develop a thyroid condition, they can also be triggered by nutrient deficiencies, heavy metal toxicity, a major illness, pregnancy, stress, and inflammation caused by poor sleep and lack of exercise.

While thyroid conditions, like hypothyroidism, are usually treated with medication, a functional medicine approach can also help heal this important gland.

Try incorporating a holistic medicine routine into your day to help reduce symptoms and support your thyroid:

Does anyone else live life on the edge 👋? ( And by on the edge we mean, eat ice cream sundaes with a dairy intolerance…)

Food allergies affect over 32 million Americans, making it likely that many of us suffer from symptoms brought on by food sensitivities or allergies.

While many food allergies appear in childhood, the root cause of others can often be traced back to a weakening of the intestinal lining that leads to an increase in space between cells in the intestinal tract—also known as leaky gut.

➡️What’s the difference between a food allergy and a food intolerance?

Food allergies: Your body recognizes the inflammatory ingredient as an invader and thinks you need additional antibodies to protect your health. IgE antibodies send messages to other immune system cells which causes an allergic reaction or anaphylaxis. This response may cause you to go into shock and it can be fatal.

Food intolerance: While usually not fatal, this response often affects the digestive system and causes micro-inflammations in the intestinal tissue. This inflammation can have an effect on your whole body which explains why some people get symptoms like a runny nose.

A functional medicine practice, like Parsley Health, will test for suspected food allergies with blood tests and/or a skin prick. You may also try an elimination diet which slowly removes and adds back in ingredients to determine the culprit of your symptoms.

Head to our link in bio to learn more about taking a holistic medicine approach to managing food sensitivities and symptoms.

Why isn’t it enough to test your TSH levels?

When it comes to your thyroid, conventional medicine practices usually start with your TSH levels. TSH is a hormone produced in the brain that tells the thyroid gland to make more T3 and T4 thyroid hormones in response to environmental factors. It is important to know your TSH levels, however, TSH isn’t enough to determine the status of your overall thyroid health.

Functional medicine providers, like Parsley Health, offer a more comprehensive panel of tests to get to the root cause of thyroid issues. By covering a wider breadth of hormones, clinicians are able to spot unusual ranges—and note any changes.

Lab tests are one of the most important tools in your prevention kit. Essential tests also reveal inflammatory markers and deficiencies in key nutrients like Vitamin D.

Head to our link in bio to learn even more about thyroid health.

HYPOthyroidism versus HYPERthyroidism—what’s the difference (and how can functional medicine help relieve symptoms?)

Both of these conditions center around the thyroid. This butterfly shaped gland produces hormones that control the body’s energy levels. Everything from metabolism, to heart rate, to even mood are affected by the thyroid.

When Parsley Health members start experiencing symptoms like unusual weight changes, irregular moods, and heart rate issues our clinicians look for the root cause, which often includes taking a deep dive into thyroid health.

Both hypothyroidism and hyperthyroidism share *some* symptoms. However, they are different.

Hyperthyroidism: When the thyroid gland produces excessive hormones and speeds up the metabolism.
Hypothyroidism: When the thyroid gland produces less hormones than normal and slows the metabolism.

Thyroid disorders can be managed using holistic medicine. Lifestyle changes like trying the Mediterranean diet, managing stress, and sleeping 7–9 hours a night may have a positive effect on your hormonal, and overall, health.

✨Comment THYROID to get more info about how to test your thyroid (and how to heal your symptoms too!)

What’s at the root cause of frustrating symptoms like fatigue, acne, and unusual weight changes? If you were to ask a Parsley Health clinician, they’d likely suggest checking your thyroid.

The thyroid—the small, butterfly-shaped gland at the base of your neck—produces hormones that regulate many functions in your body. When something is up with your thyroid, you may start noticing other symptoms like:

Thyroid tests are a key part of a functional medicine approach. These results can help determine if you’re experiencing a thyroid condition like hyperthyroidism, hypothyroidism, Hashimoto’s, or Grave’s disease.

Is your period cycle changing? 🤔⁠
⁠
Some shifts to look out for include:⁠
-Your period disappears for a cycle or two.⁠
-Your period starts closer or further apart from your last bleed.⁠
-You have period cycles where your ovaries don’t release an egg (in other words, you don’t ovulate). ⁠
⁠
The root cause of these changes in your cycle may point back to perimenopause AKA the time before your body enters menopause. One of the ways Parsley Health clinicians know that a patient has entered menopause is when they haven’t reported a period for 12 months.⁠
⁠
Perimenopause lasts about four years on average—and the cycle of symptoms can be frustrating. A functional medicine approach may help balance hormones and bring some relief. ⁠
⁠
If you suspect you’re in perimenopause try these tips:⁠
-Prioritize daily meditation and breathwork. ⁠
-Move mindfully—do high intensity workouts in moderation due to their impact on cortisol. ⁠
-Try adaptogenic herbs that support the adrenal gland’s function. ⁠
⁠
Head to our link in bio to get an in-depth resource for a holistic medicine approach to hormonal changes

This month, the F.D.A. officially banned the use of Red Dye No. 3 in foods sold in the U.S.

Scientific evidence links chemical food dyes, often used in ultraprocessed foods, to a host of health issues—especially in kids—including gut dysbiosis, endocrine disruption, hyperactivity and ADHD symptoms, and cancer (in animal studies).

So, why does it take so long to get these substances banned? 
Health advocates have been raising concerns about food dyes like Red No. 3 for decades. And they’ve been successful in many countries—many of these dyes are already banned in Europe, the UK, Australia and New Zealand. Big food companies like Kellogg’s make healthier versions of their products to sell in those markets; Canadian Froot Loops, for example, are colored with concentrated fruit and vegetable juices.

The FDA is finally updating U.S. guidelines after a public outcry surrounding studies showing male lab rats exposed to high levels of the Red No. 3 developed thyroid cancer.

But the ban won’t take effect right away. Manufacturers have until 2027 to remove the chemical from their products.

So what should you do to protect yourself in the meantime and avoid other harmful dyes not affected by the ban (like Red 40, Yellow 5, and Blue 1)?

- Read ingredient labels to check for artificial dyes. The Environmental Working Group has a great database. 
- Avoid worst-offender foods. Ultra Processed cereals, candy, cookies, and cakes often use these dyes. One more reason to opt for whole, or minimally processed alternatives. 
- Beware of unexpected offenders. Even “healthy” foods like vegan meat alternatives and gummy vitamins can contain artificial dyes. Make sure to check labels.

A fascination with natural shapes, colours and patterns draws humans to the natural world, just as we at Novellini are inspired by it when designing our products and creating our finishes.
Artist @bernulia, also from Mantua, uses mankind’s need for beauty as a common thread to create chromatically harmonious compositions.
Soggetto preferito dal 2020

Quando ieri @bernulia sui propri social ha svelato il nome del suo nuovissimo spazio creativo @gattorosso_studio ci è scappato un sorriso compiaciuto, perché quando qualche settimana fa siamo stati a trovarla era stata proprio lei di persona ad anticiparcelo, raccontandoci di quel gatto rosso che aveva suscitato interesse e curiosità in tutto il quartiere creando empatia e unione tra tutti i suoi abitanti. 

Ed è proprio qui, nel suo nuovo studio dove siamo stati i primi a fotografarla, che noi abbiamo conosciuto Giulia per l’occasione in compagnia dell’amico e designer di interni @jesuismatteoaroldi . Dopo aver realizzato la meraviglia di questo posto, dove si respira arte e creatività in ogni angolo, in un’atmosfera accogliente, abbiamo iniziato a realizzare i primi ritratti utilizzando la sola luce emanata dalle bellissime candele sparse per il tavolo di lavoro. 

La mattinata tra uno scatto e l’altro è letteralmente volata, anche perché ascoltare Giulia raccontarci come e da dove nasce il suo flusso creativo è un privilegio che non abbiamo voluto farci scappare. La sua arte è finita in copertina sul Washington Post ed è diventata comunicazione per marchi importantissimi come Barilla, Amazon, Siemens e moltissimi altri e noi abbiamo provato nel nostro piccolo, a raccontarvi chi c’è dietro alle opere che sicuramente tutti voi avreste visto almeno una volta.

Dr. Murad wants to know whether you prefer RetinOL or RetinAL 🤔✨ Don’t know the difference? ⬇️

Both are Vitamin A derivatives that boost collagen, fight wrinkles, and speed up cell turnover. But for the specifics:

💚 RetinOL: Improves skin tone + texture, works for visible signs of aging (wrinkles + dullness), and is best for first-time retinoid users.

✅ RetinAL: Works at a faster cell-turnover rate, works for more dramatic signs of aging (sagging + deep wrinkles), and is best for experienced retinoid users.

So which one are you reaching for during your night routine?

Acne-prone + oily skin 🤝 dry + sensitive

The fight against childhood hunger in America started with the Black community with the Black Panther Party and the free breakfast program in 1969. Since then, Black trailblazers like Shirley Chisholm and Fanny Lou have inspired, educated and fought for food-justice nationwide.

Today, we recognize and applaud Black hunger heroes, like Rosie Jackson in Louisiana, Stella Ndahura in California, Valrie Baker in New York, and Betty Wiggins in Texas who are strong leaders dedicated to nourishing our kids' future and dreams. Our work is focused on partnering with schools and communities nationwide to help feed kids. We do this by providing grants, working to change policies and systems that we know work and can help eradicate childhood hunger. 🧡

In honor of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., let's remember his enduring vision - a world where equality spans all aspects of life, including access to nutritious food for all children. 🌟 Join us as we strive to make #NoKidHungry more than a hashtag -- a reality. #MLKDay

Hunger does not have one distinct look. While some kids and teens may not "look" hungry, it doesn't negate the fact that they are. The bottom line is that nearly 1 in 5 youth across the nation are experiencing hunger.

Some of these children are missing meals; others are faced with hunger-related hardship as their families make tradeoffs between buying enough groceries or paying bills. That's why we do the work we do. 🧡

Our @billyshore spent the last few days in LA witnessing the resilience and heroism of the community coming together to ensure no kid goes hungry in the face of the LA Fires. This is his story: 

Earlier this week, I spent time at the base camp for first responders to the Palisades fire. This temporary city supports over 1,100 firefighters, police officers and members of the National Guard.

When I arrived, I was invited to ride in a fire department brush truck to see the neighborhood devastation. Nothing we hadn’t seen on the news, but unlike the news, it wasn’t over in a few minutes and there was no changing the channel. We spent hours walking among thousands of destroyed homes. The intensity of the fire and the ferocity of its wind-driven spread left an impression TV can’t. 

In Pasadena, at the @daylaborernetowrk food pantry, where No Kid Hungry has provided support, I saw people come together in times of need. Volunteers unloaded an 18-wheeler packed with bread, soup, water, diapers, and other essentials. This food pantry, located at a job center for day laborers—many of them immigrants who are hesitant to seek government assistance—serves families now living in shelters, cars and even garages after losing everything.

In the evening, we joined Mary Sue Milliken and the team from @wckitchen at the Arboretum, serving meals to evacuees. Families lined up for beef teriyaki, mac and cheese or rockfish salad, along with all the tangerines they could carry. 

The challenges of recovery and rebuilding are mind-boggling. Toxic debris has to be cleared, homes have to be rebuilt, and families have to begin again. Through it all we’ll ensure that children don’t miss a meal.

Our CA team is working tirelessly to assess where we can have the greatest impact. Through the newly launched L.A. Wildfire Response Fund, we’ll partner with organizations like NDLON, World Central Kitchen and others to ensure that families receive the food and support they need to rebuild.

Everyone has a strength to share—and everyone has a role to play. Whether donating, volunteering or simply spreading the word, you’re a part of this effort.

Thank you for being a part of this important work.
When we feed our children, we are feeding our future. 🥪📝

Ending childhood hunger has always been "in." 🤝💪

At No Kid Hungry, $1 can help provide 10 meals for kids. A common misconception is that we buy and give food to communities and schools, but we don't buy food at all. The biggest problem is ensuring that children have reliable access to the food they need to thrive. We do this in multiple ways, including:

🧡 Supporting school and community meals programs

🧡 Providing grants to schools and communities

🧡 Advocate for better laws and policies

When we carefully invest donor dollars in this work, schools and communities can feed a lot more kids. Share ↗️ this post with a friend to spread the word! #NoKidHungry

Thanks to generous donors like you, the No Kid Hungry campaign helped millions of children get the nutritious food they need to nourish their bodies, dream big, and reach their full potential. 🤝

From July 2023 to June 2024, we granted more than $18 million to school districts, community groups, and other organizations; and during the school year, No Kid Hungry grantees served more than 374 million meals to kids and families.

Tis the season for tretinoin. ❄️ Many of us are cycling retinoids back into our routine to deal with post-summer dark spots and skin dullness.

With great retinoid power comes great responsibility to your skin barrier. Given retinoids can be drying, it’s especially important to care for your barrier during the colder months.

➕Apply to dry skin. Damp skin is more absorbant and can intensify tretinoin’s effects, especially when first starting out. Cleanse skin and wait 10-20 minute before applying a pea size amount.
➕ Make a retinoid sandwich to minimize irritation. Apply Activating Serum first, then your retinoid, following by Triple Lipid-Peptide Cream.
➕ SPF as a non-negotiable. Look for one that’s broad-spectrum, at least 30 SPF (even higher, even better!) and fragrance-free. Bonus points for a hydrating formula with ceramides and glycerin to counteract dryness.

___________________________________
According to Variety, Biden was previously represented by CAA from 2017 to 2020, after serving as Vice President for eight years. During that time, he published a bestselling memoir, headlined numerous speaking engagements, and embarked on the 42-date “American Promise Tour,” which sold over 85,000 tickets.

We’re thrilled to announce that our Spinal Decompression service is now available in our Maryland market! 🙌

Spinal decompression is a non-surgical, comfortable therapy designed to relieve back, leg, neck, or arm pain caused by herniated discs, sciatica, or other injuries. By gently stretching the spine, this therapy helps reduce pressure on the spinal discs, promoting healing and pain relief.

Come experience this revolutionary treatment, available at our Essex and Hyattsville locations!

Learn more about spinal decompression therapy and how it can help you get back to doing what you love. Explore the benefits and book your session today: https://bit.ly/Excelsiainjurycare-spinal-decompression-therapy

Roscoe Village, let’s be honest—it’s cold. That bone-deep, soul-crushing kind of cold that makes you question why you didn’t just move to San Diego when you had the chance. But hey, here you are. The upside? We’ve got something that’ll make you forget all about your frostbitten fingers and the sound of ice cracking underfoot.

A steaming bowl of beef, miso, mushrooms, and rice noodles—rich, earthy, and unapologetically bold. It’s finished with a touch of micro shiso for that subtle, unexpected kick that takes it from “just soup” to something far more satisfying. This isn’t just a dish; it’s a statement. A reminder that even in the face of sub-zero hell, you can find something worth savoring.

And if you’re smart (you are), you’ll pair it with a high-elevation Syrah. Think big, spicy, and gutsy—everything that stands up to the miso’s umami and the beef’s depth without flinching. It’s the kind of combo that makes you want to hole up, pour another glass, and forget the outside world exists for a while.

So, do yourself a favor. When the wind howls, and you can’t feel your toes, don’t just endure—rebel. Swing by LUSH, grab a bowl, and let winter know it can’t beat you. At least not while you’ve got this kind of firepower in your corner.

A Typical Day in the LUSH Test Kitchen

Well, here we are again. Another day in the LUSH test kitchen, surrounded by the finest ingredients, tools of the trade, and…existential dread. Why are we here? No, really—why are we here? Is it to perfect the ratio of truffle oil to aioli? To test if microgreens truly elevate a dish? Or is it all just a futile dance of flavors, a beautiful charade meant to distract us from the void?

But then—light bulb moment—we take a bite. The recipe clicks. Suddenly, the universe aligns, and for one fleeting moment, it all makes sense. Yes, this is why we’re here: to create something that stirs the soul, that makes people close their eyes and whisper, “Damn, that’s good.”

Do our recipes mean anything in the grand cosmic scheme? Probably not. But if we can deliver a perfect pairing or a soup that feels like a warm hug, maybe—just maybe—that’s enough. Now, back to work. The micro shiso isn’t going to garnish itself.

We’ve all been there — the heart-sinking moment when you look at your marksheet and realise things didn’t go as planned.

For many, it raises the daunting question: What next? In a society where academic success and competitive exams like UPSC often define self-worth, it’s easy to lose hope.

For Jigyasu Agarwal, the third attempt was his final one. Looking at his marksheet in 2022 was heartbreaking, but it also marked the start of a new chapter.

After two failed attempts, he decided to seek purpose beyond UPSC and return to the corporate world.

The journey was far from easy. Finding a job proved challenging, and Jigyasu spent months upskilling through online courses. “I struggled with finding my niche,” he shares.

In August 2023, his perseverance paid off when he secured a job at a political consultancy firm. His cousin, Akshat Agarwal, had walked a similar path a few years earlier. That’s when the realisation struck: he wasn’t alone in this struggle.

To address that, together, they founded 'Rebounce' in October 2023 to help others facing the same challenges.

Rebounce provides a ‘second chance', offering guidance and mentorship to ex-UPSC aspirants, helping them pivot into public policy, consulting, NGOs, and more.

To date, they’ve helped over 300 former aspirants secure jobs in public policy, impact consulting, and corporations, equipping them with the tools and confidence to thrive in alternative career paths.

A new chapter in wildlife conservation has begun with the birth of eight wolf pups at Karnataka’s first-ever Wolf Sanctuary in Bankapur. 

This moment marks a significant victory for the Indian grey wolf, a keystone predator that plays a crucial role in maintaining ecological balance.

Since its establishment in 2021, the 332-hectare sanctuary has become a refuge not only for wolves but also for other species, including leopards, peacocks, blackbucks, and more.

With the announcement of the pups’ birth, the Karnataka Forest Department’s efforts in ensuring the safety and well-being of the wolves are being hailed as a success.

Wolves, often overshadowed by larger predators like tigers and lions, are finally receiving the attention they deserve, thanks to the safe haven provided by the sanctuary.

It’s a clear signal that expanding such areas is the need of the hour for wildlife conservation.

Here's to the wolves and every species whose survival we must protect!

Despite representing 10% of India’s population, queer communities receive only 1% of global philanthropic funding, according to a report by Dasra.

This statistic reveals a harsh reality—only a few of India’s wealthiest philanthropists prioritise LGBTQIA+ issues.

But the queer community is much more than just data. While conversations around diversity and equity have gained momentum, tangible support for LGBTQIA+ communities remains limited.

Yet, amidst this challenge, a beacon of hope shines bright. Three visionary philanthropists have come together to launch the Pride Fund, a corporate philanthropic initiative aimed at uplifting queer-led organisations across India.

With a generous annual pledge of Rs 2 crore, the fund is set to support grassroots initiatives and amplify queer voices that have long been silenced.

The Keshav Suri Foundation, Godrej Industries Group, and Radhika Piramal stand united in their commitment, empowering eight queer-led organisations — Basera Social Institute, Deepshikha Committee, Vikalp (Women’s Group), Sappho for Equality, Karna Subarna Welfare Society, Ya_All: The Youth Network, Chhattisgarh Mitwa Sankalp Samiti, and Payana — that provide life-changing services such as livelihood training, legal aid, shelter, and crisis care.

Piramal, who champions the cause, said, “The Pride Fund aims to raise both resources and awareness for queer-led NGOs that work tirelessly to support the community.”

Godrej Industries, for its part, is one of the more progressive companies in terms of Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion, with nearly 250 of its 40,000 employees openly embracing their identities.

This initiative marks a crucial step toward ensuring meaningful change — one that amplifies queer voices and strengthens the organizations working to create a more inclusive future.

Ananya Prasad, a 34-year-old from Bengaluru and of Indian origin, achieved a historic milestone by becoming the first woman of colour to row solo across any ocean.

Her 3,000-mile, 52-day journey began on December 11, 2024, when she set off from La Gomera in the Canary Islands. She arrived in Antigua in the Caribbean on February 1, 2025, having rowed an estimated 60–70 kilometres each day across the Atlantic.

Despite having no prior nautical experience, Ananya demonstrated extraordinary determination. She dedicated three and a half years to rigorous training, building her physical endurance, technical rowing skills, and mental resilience.

This preparation proved crucial when, during the race, her rudder broke. Undeterred, she braved 20-knot winds and her fear of deep water to dive under her boat and make the necessary repairs.

She also regularly cleared barnacles from the hull to maintain speed and had to navigate the challenges of encounters with whales, orcas, and flying fish.

Ananya's remarkable feat culminated in completing the World's Toughest Row, where she finished second in the solo category.

Driven by a desire to make a difference, Ananya undertook this challenge to raise funds for two important causes: the Mental Health Foundation and the Deenabandhu Trust, which provides a home and education for orphaned and impoverished children in South India.

In 1956, the world of cinema was introduced to a performance that would leave an indelible mark on the history of film. 

Chunibala Devi, a retired stage actress, defied age to bring the character of Indir Thakrun to life in Satyajit Ray’s Pather Panchali.

Despite being 80 and living in Kolkata’s red-light district, she delivered a performance that New York Herald Tribune described as “fantastically realistic and effective”.
But how did she land this role?

The casting process for Pather Panchali was a challenging one for Ray, who struggled to find the right actress to portray the wizened, old Indir Thakrun.

It was Reba Devi, who played Mrs. Mukherjee in the film, who recommended Chunibala Devi. Upon meeting her at a house in Kolkata’s red-light district, Ray was struck by her presence and knew immediately she was the perfect choice for the role.

Despite her frail health and years away from the screen, she agreed to step out of retirement, bringing life to one of the most iconic characters in world cinema.

Chunibala’s dedication to her craft was extraordinary. She performed despite her deteriorating health, even taking a small dose of opium each afternoon to keep going, a practice that became part of her routine on set.

At 82, she filmed her final scene — a death scene so perfect that Ray rushed to cradle her head in his lap as soon as it hit the ground.

Her performance was so compelling that it earned her the Best Actress award at the Manila Film Festival, making her the first Indian to win an award in the Best Actor/Actress category at an international film festival.

But tragically, she passed away in 1955, just before Pather Panchali made its debut on the world stage.

Her work would live on as an unforgettable piece of cinema history.

What happens when two childhood friends with a shared love for travel decide to solve a major problem? They build a startup that’s changing the way India travels!

Meet Rohan Verma and Shubhangi Pandey, co-founders of JustWravel, a travel startup that began with a simple idea: affordable and safe travel for young Indians. From schoolmates in Lucknow to successful entrepreneurs, their journey is nothing short of inspiring.

Armed with engineering and MBA degrees, Rohan and Shubhangi identified a “lack of affordable and safe travel options for group travellers, especially women,” and turned it into an opportunity.

Quitting their stable jobs, they pooled ₹6 lakh and launched JustWravel in 2016. Their fixed-departure group tours brought together solo travellers to explore India’s beauty, fostering unforgettable adventures and a thriving travel community.

From trekking in the Himalayas and exploring beaches to offbeat cultural tours and now corporate travel, their curated trips focus on affordability, safety, and unique experiences.

With domestic trips starting at just ₹6,500 and international ones from ₹32,000, JustWravel has become a go-to choice for millennials and Gen Z looking for adventure without breaking the bank.

In the beginning, the duo handled everything themselves—marketing, operations, sales—sometimes operating at a loss just to keep their promise to travellers.

Fast forward to FY24, JustWravel has crossed ₹13 crore in annual revenue, served 50,000+ travellers, and expanded into corporate travel with clients like Shiv Nadar Foundation and Jawa & Yezdi Bikes.

Now, they’re on a mission to scale even further—expanding their destinations from 50 to 150, integrating AI for personalised travel, and targeting ₹28 crore by the end of the year.

A wonderful example of a Stick Style Victorian home. Stick Style is named after the use of linear “stickwork” on the outside walls which mimic an exposed half-timber frame. It was a totally American concept! Stick Style homes also tend to have tall windows, multiple stories, surface ornaments, sharply pitched roofs, and towers. This home certainly demonstrates each of those features. Are you a fan?

The gorgeous Joseph Webb House, one of three historic houses in Old Wethersfield @webbdeanestevens museum! The Joseph Webb house was built in 1752 and served as George Washington’s headquarters where he met with the French commander, the Comte de Rochambeau, to finalize the joint military campaign that led to victory in Yorktown, which ended the American Revolution. George Washington DID sleep here for five nights during this time!

Visit this fascinating home as well as the other Webb-Deane-Stevens properties. Another great reason to visit Old Wethersfield!

#localconnecticut #wethersfieldct #ctrealtor

It’s starting to look like spring out there! This is known as the Bunce House in Granby, CT. A little Google search tells me the home was built circa 1814 for Isaac Phelps, a wealthy farmer. He raised five children here with his wife Rhoda. Over the years it changed hands to the Dibbles, and a Dibble daughter named Laura married Jonathan Bunce. They inherited the home in 1883, and they lived in Hartford but summered in Granby. Every summer they would move their furnitire on a wagon to Granby. Can you imagine?! Summering in Granby seems a bit comical now but at the time it was fashionable to summer in the country, and of course you weren’t flying or driving off to more exotic locales. I particularly love the front fence of this home. Zoom in for the details!

I’ve grown more than 7M followers, and I’ve realized:

The number 1 part of growth is your content strategy…

Here are the 3 foundations of a viral content strategy in any niche:

1️⃣Type of posts:

Posts have 1 of 3 goals:

1.1. Get you seen (Awareness)
1.2. Get you liked (Nurture)
1.3. Get you paid (Conversions)

When creating a post, you must know what its purpose is from the beginning

Generally, the more generic the topic is, the more awareness it tends to generate

But awareness-type content isn't enough - you must also Nurture your audience. Otherwise, they won't trust you

Here's where personal content comes into play

Think of “How I did something” vs “How to”

And lastly, likes don’t pay our bills. That’s why we have Conversion (💰)

Turning all the attention and trust into cash 

This is a type of post I recommend you keep to your Stories as much as possible, but during a product launch or every once in a while, it doesn’t hurt (check my pinned posts for examples of how I integrate it in my posts)

2️⃣ Frequency:
👉This is pretty self-explanatory.

Focus on feed first (minimum of 3 weekly feed posts, optimal 7)

Stories are your second priority (and that's if you have at least a few thousand followers)

Neglect Lives (unless you have a massive audience and want to sell/nurture it) 

Go for sustainable quality. Don't be a perfectionist; don't post for the sake of posting, either. It's all about balance

1️⃣Type of posts:
👉Instagram in 2024 has never been more balanced.

All formats can give you a viral result.

That’s why I recommend trying them all.

But strategically 👇

Start with a balanced approach—33/33/33 split between formats.

If you post daily, that’s ten posts of each format each month. 

Then, do this for ~ three months and gather all the data…

Afterwards, look for trends. Did one format:

✅Get more engagement per reach than the others?

✅Take significantly more time to make?

✅Bring you more enjoyment when making?

With these factors in mind, update your content ratio

Throughout Black History Month we will be highlighting team members who talk about Black History.

Today we will spotlight our team member Ehleria Hernandez.

When asked: What is your advice to young Black professionals who may want to follow your career path? She said "Personally, having a mentor at my workplace has been invaluable, providing a trusted figure to turn to for professional advice and emotional support.

Embrace feedback without taking it personally. THAT IS KEY! Feedback is one way to improve opportunities and allow growth. Embrace the discomfort of growth, for the challenges lies the path to becoming the best version of yourself.

Lastly, prioritize self-care to maintain a healthy work-life balance. Seek support when needed and don't hesitate to take breaks. Maintaining a healthy mental state enhances your professional efficiency, so it’s important to mentally disconnect from work after hours and recharge."

이 소중한 이야기는 오랫동안 가족과 가까운 이들 곁에서 조용히 간직해왔습니다. 늘 제 삶과 여정을 여러분과 나누는 걸 좋아했지만, 이번만큼은 제 마음 가까이에 두고 싶었던 순간이었어요. 

이 이야기는 단순히 반지나 프로포즈에 관한 것이 아닙니다. 작은 순간들이 쌓여 특별한 무언가의 토대가 된 사랑에 대한 이야기입니다. 평생을 함께하고 싶은 사람을 만났다는 것이 얼마나 큰 축복인지, 하루하루 새삼 느끼고 있어요. 

앞으로도 편안하고 행복한 방식으로 조금씩 더 이야기를 나눌게요. 항상 따뜻한 응원을 보내주신 여러분, 그리고 이번 특별한 순간을 함께 축하해 주시는 모든 분들께 진심으로 감사드립니다. 아직도 믿기지 않아요…

February is #BlackHistoryMonth, sometimes called Black Futures Month, a time to acknowledge that the story of Black people in the US is still being written, and find ways to honor the many successes and contributions of African-Americans both in the past and today. 

Swipe for ideas on how to increase your understanding of the Black experience in the US.

If you identify as Black, focusing on Black history may feel inspiring or healing, or because the history of Black people in the US contains so much injustice, focusing on it can bring up challenging emotions. All of these feelings are valid, and you can choose to engage, or not, in whatever way feels right to you.

Self love is the assignment 💕 On Valentine’s Day and every day, shower yourself with affection and appreciation with these self-love ideas. Loving yourself is an essential part of healthy relationships with others, and supports your mental health too!

One-sided relationships can take a toll on your emotional and physical well-being, often leading to feelings of anxiety, resentment, and low self-worth. 💔 

When you invest significantly more time and effort than your partner, it can create an unhealthy dynamic that leaves you feeling drained and unappreciated. 

Recognizing the signs of imbalance in a relationship is essential so that both partners can feel valued, loved, respected, and understood.

Learn more about the signs and how to fix a one-sided relationship at the link in bio.

Eating disorders are complex, serious, and often misunderstood. Swipe through to learn key facts – like how eating disorders often develop alongside mental health conditions like anxiety and depression, OCD and ADHD, and how anyone can develop an eating disorder regardless of gender, age, race, and body size.

Burberry Winter 2025

‘Think of them as weekend-escapees. It’s that great Friday-night exodus from London to the countryside for long rainy walks and to disconnect in the great outdoors. It’s day-trips to grand stately homes.’ – Daniel Lee

Presented in London at Tate Britain – a fitting backdrop for a celebration of British creativity – Daniel Lee’s latest collection is inspired by weekends in the country, long rainy walks in the great outdoors and the interiors of grand stately homes. Rendering coats and scarves, evening wear, daywear and suits in a mix of twisted fabrics by British makers, the collection is grounded in Burberry’s values of design, innovation and skill.

⛔KIRKLARELİ MÜFTÜSÜ
ADNAN ZEKİ BIYIK’IN KANDİL MESAJI:

⛔Sorular geliyor zaman zaman, “Hocam bu kandil gecesinde kaç rekat namaz kılalım, kaç bin tevhid , zikir çekelim”. "Ben de samimi Müslüman kardeşlerime diyorum ki":

⛔Size daha kazançlı ama nefse ağır gelen sevap kazanma yolları göstereyim mi?

-Evet Hocam göster.

Öyleyse şu söylediklerimi yapın!

⛔1-Variyetiniz varsa alın birkaç yetimi tepeden tırnağa kadar giydirin, yedirin içirin, uzun vadede ise o yetimlerin temel ihtiyaç ve eğitim masraflarını karşılayın. Okuyup büyük adam olsunlar, dine, vatana millete topluma faydalı gençler olsunlar. Zaten sevgiden şefkatten ve baba himayesinden mahrum kalmışlar. Bunların sizin yüzünüze sevgi ile bir bakışı Allah'ın size rahmet nazarı ile bakması demektir. Malumunuz Aziz Peygamberimiz, duası reddolunmayan güruhun içinde yetimi en başta saymıştır. “Mazlumun bedduasından, ahından ve yetimin gözyaşlarından sakının. Çünkü insanlar rahat uykuda iken onlar dert, sıkıntı, üzüntü içindedirler" (Buhari)
⛔2-Beşinci, onuncu veya bilmem kaçıncı umrenizi yapmayı bırakın, burada harcayacağınız paranızı, evine kurbandan kurbana et giren komşularınıza bağışlayabilirsiniz. Bu gerçekten beratınıza vesile olabilecektir.
⛔3-Zenginseniz eğer, gece bin rekat namaz kılmaktan daha içerikli bir sevap önerebilirim size,,, okuluna giden yavrusuna harçlık verebilmek için kendisi 5 km yolu yaya giden gariban babalara yardım yapabilirsiniz…çok uzakta değil,,,çevremizde bu insanlardan çok var…
⛔4-Bu gece, hastane köşelerinde yatan nice kimsesiz hastaları ziyaret edip sevindirebilirsiniz, bunlar beratın ruhuna çok uygun davranışlardır…
⛔5-Zenginseniz eğer çevrenizdeki tüm gariplere, mağdurlara, mazlumlara ve yoksullara bu akşam güzel bir lokantada güzel bir yemek yedirebilirsiniz…
⛔6-Zengin fakir fark etmez, bugün hastanelerde can bekleyen, kan bekleyen onbinlerce hastadan birine şifa olabilecek bir veya bir kaç ünite kan bağışlayabilirsiniz… Bu da 1000 rekât nafile namaza eş değerdir…
⛔7-Bu Berat Gecesini vesile ederek sizi büyütünceye kadar sayısız eziyetler çeken, huzurevine attığınız anne veya babanızı oradan çıkarıp duasını alabilir ya da ziyaret edebilirsiniz.

Bu büyüleyici dağ kasabasında damakları şenlendirecek harika restoranlar var! İşte mutlaka denemen gereken yerler:

⭐ Smithy’s Tavern – Rahat atmosferi ve leziz burgerleriyle ünlü. 🍔
⭐ Au Montagnard – Ahşap dekorasyonlu samimi bir ortamda fondü keyfi. 🫕

Based in Miami and founded in 2011, @elcarwash is Florida’s largest express car wash and soon a top operator in Michigan, borne out of entrepreneurship.  “My co-founder @bigjefek and I were working in private equity when he came across some opportunities in the car wash sector,” shares co-founder @justinlandau. “At a wedding, he mentioned a company in Miami and said, ‘We should take a look at this business. It’s one of the best I’ve ever seen.’ We spent some time looking into it further and immediately agreed that we needed to acquire it and build the business.”

From that moment, both Geoff Karas and Justin Landau quit their jobs in New York City and placed all their bets on El Car Wash in 2019. As the two raised the funds along the way, the original investors agreed to support the business duo, but only if they ran the company themselves. 

So what did they do? They packed their bags and moved to Miami.

El Car Wash has since then transformed the car wash experience with cutting-edge technology, eco-friendly practices, and unbeatable service. Their unlimited wash programs, premium amenities, and commitment to employees and the community make the homegrown company stand out. 

“We were at the forefront of understanding the power of membership and with our finance backgrounds quickly got a handle on the analytics of the business,” Justin continues. “That combined with a strong eye for branding and marketing let to a clear vision of what the brand should look and feel like and a framework for the entire brand.” 
Proudly the Official Car Wash of the Stanley Cup Champion @flapanthers and @detroitlionsnfl, El Car Wash also partners with UCF Athletics, @baptisthealthsf, and more. With over 60 locations throughout Florida and Michigan, El Car Wash has plans to continue expanding beyond the two states and across the continent.

Strawberry Coconut Sparkle – A Glam Galentine’s Mocktail (Recipe Below & in Bio)

  Valentine’s Day is literally around the corner, and what better way to celebrate than with a refreshing, mocktail with your girls?! 

  Strawberry Coconut Sparkle is the ultimate Galentine’s drink—light, sweet, and with a hint of zest, all while keeping the calories in check. Plus, the edible glitter makes it extra glamorous 💅🏾 

💕 Only 61-69 Calories per Glass! 💕

Ingredients

	•	1 can coconut cream (for rimming the glass + a touch inside the drink)
	•	Monk fruit sugar (for a naturally sweet rim)
	•	1 lime (sliced)
	•	Fresh strawberries (chopped)
	•	Humm Probiotic Kombucha BLUEBERRY MINT (or your favorite sparkling drink) @hummkombucha 
	•	Edible glitter (for that sparkle ✨)

Instructions

	1.	Rim the glass – Dip the rim of your glass into coconut cream, then coat it with monk fruit sugar for a sweet touch.
	2.	Muddle the fruit – In a glass or jar, mash together sliced lime and strawberries with a spoon to release their natural flavors. Stir in a small spoonful of coconut cream for a smooth, creamy balance.
	3.	Pour in the fizz – Add your choice of Humm Probiotic Kombucha or any sparkling drink you love.
	4.	Add the magic – Sprinkle a dash of edible glitter into the drink and stir gently for that extra shimmer.
	5.	Sip & Enjoy! – Gather your besties, toast to sisterhood, and enjoy your Strawberry Coconut Sparkle!

Cheers to love, friendship, and all the sparkle in between! ✨💖

Jesus 
It’s no surprise your mother gave you the name Jesus. You were gentle and kind and loving, quiet and unassuming, but so powerful, and your presence was felt the minute you walked into any room. You never demanded the spotlight. You never needed to make a sound to be recognized, your heart and your talent did that as effortlessly as you artistry did. I’ve been having trouble putting the words together the last few days. The truth is I’m still in shock that such a beautiful young life has come to an end. It seems senseless and unfair. I know your family is brokenhearted as am I and everyone else who knew you. Your spirit moved on to the next phase beyond this life but I know wherever you are there is beauty and light. And the beauty and light you left here will live on forever. Rest in peace, sweet angel… 💔

I love you beyond forever 🥥🥥

At this point I think they’re just fucking with us.

They released a new batch of wolves a couple weeks ago in Colorado, right onto a friend’s ranch.  He found this elk leg in the snow after neighbors spotted the wolves on the prowl. 
He has livestock on his land and no one even bothered to alert him as to what they were planning.  He said he thinks it was 5 wolves.  This is only 30 minutes outside of Aspen. 

I’m a fan of wolves, and all wildlife, but I think ballot box biology is a terrible idea.  Most of these people all gung ho for the reintroduction have no idea what they’ve voted for. 

There’s a reason why they eradicated wolves from the west ages ago, and a reason why they’re the bad guys in every old fairy tale from little red riding hood to the 3 little pigs. 
They’re brilliant, ruthless hunters, and they will kill and eat everything they can, including cattle, horses and dogs. 

Aspen is going to get very weird in the upcoming years, and I’m sure many people are going to regret this decision. 

They’ll have to eventually allow wolf hunting when the numbers get too high, but good luck hunting them or even finding them if they don’t want to be found.

Cooking with Mila episode 4: Miracle Rice with Chicken…so easy and so good! #recipes #food #cooking 

Ingredients:
Cooking spray
1-1/2 cups uncooked rice basmati preferred
2-1/2 cups chicken broth or stock
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1 teaspoon onion powder
1/2 teaspoon dried thyme
1/2 teaspoon dried oregano
2 tablespoons dried parsley
8 tablespoons unsalted butter
3 tablespoons finely chopped fresh parsley optional, for serving
Juice of one large lemon
 
Directions:
-Set oven to 400°F. Generously spray a glass or ceramic 9x13-inch pan with cooking spray.
-Add uncooked rice, chicken broth, garlic powder, onion powder, thyme, oregano, parsley, directly into the prepared pan. Stir.
-Add the butter pieces evenly across the mixture. Cover tightly with foil.
-Bake covered for 40 minutes. Remove foil and set it aside, squeeze the lemon, stir and then add the chicken nuggets and bake uncovered for 15 more minutes.
-Remove from the oven and enjoy!

Cooking with Mila Episode 3: Stick of Butter Rice with Chicken 

Ingredients:
• 2 cups long grain white rice
• 6 oz sliced white mushrooms
• 10.5 oz can french onion soup
• (2) 10.5 oz cans beef consomme
• 1 stick of salted butter melted
• 1 cup grated pecorino romano
• 1.5 - 2 Ibs boneless skinless chicken thighs I used 5 chicken thighs
• ½ tbsp paprika
• 1 tsp complete seasoning

Directions: 
1. In a 9x13 baking dish, add in the uncooked white rice and sliced white mushrooms. 
2. In a large measuring cup or bowl, add in the can of french onion soup and both cans of beef consomme. Stir that together to combine. Pour that mixture into the baking dish over the rice and mushrooms. Then, evenly pour in the melted butter and shake the grated pecorino romano evenly over the top.
3. Now, season both sides of the chicken thighs with paprika and complete seasoning and add them right into the baking dish.
4. Cover the baking dish very tightly with aluminum foil and bake it at
350°F for 1 & ½ hours. Once It's done take it out of the oven, remove the aluminum foil, fluff the rice up using a fork, and then pop it back into the oven uncovered at 400°F for about 8-10 minutes or until browned. Enjoy!

🚨 Wedding planning rule #1: You don’t have to follow every tradition! 💍❌⁠
⁠
Gone are the days of feeling obligated to wear white, throw a bouquet, or hand out favors if they don’t feel like you. Your wedding should reflect your personality, not a rulebook!⁠
⁠
Here are 5 wedding traditions you can totally skip:⁠
⁠
✔ Ditch the white dress if it's not your style!⁠
✔ Skip the wedding party (less stress, more fun!).⁠
✔ Save money on guest favors—they usually get left behind anyway.⁠
✔ Toss the actual bouquet toss (no pressure, no awkwardness!).⁠
✔ Say goodbye to a traditional guest book—there are better ways to remember the day!⁠

Well I guess we’re getting sushi tonight!

In reality, being smart with money isn’t a choice between sushi dinner or saving money…in fact, you can do BOTH!

It’s all about knowing how to say yes without wrecking your financial goals. The key? 

Intentional spending. 

When you plan for the things you love, you’re not “splurging”—you’re spending on purpose.
So go ahead, order that spicy tuna roll. 

Just make sure your money is working for you—whether that’s through dining rewards, budgeted fun money, or a solid financial plan that makes room for joy AND growth. 

Because wealth isn’t built by cutting out sushi—it’s built by making every dollar count.

Did you know that although many of #NoKidHungry's efforts are directed towards schools and community groups, we also support food banks? From this work with food banks nationwide, we have learned that not everyone understands the differences between a food bank and a food pantry, so let's break it down! ✍️

Food banks are nonprofit facilities that store food to be delivered to various food programs and other facilities within their community, this includes food pantries. A food pantry is an independent, volunteer-run community space that provides families with food from food banks. Both work to serve those in their communities by providing food and other resources for those in need.

For more on food banks and food pantries, tap the link in bio. https://bit.ly/3l3QxuX

Since the summer of 2023, Fish Community Food Bank has been able to distribute a week's worth of meals to families in their community. Before this change, children were required to eat each meal on site, which kept many families from making the trip to the meal distribution centers.

The increase in meals served has been exponential. In 2021, before the flexibility was implemented, they only served 11,000 meals to kids during the summer. By 2024, they were serving 36,000 meals to kids!

The significant impact of the summer meals program would not be possible without the support from everybody in the community. The food bank has strong relationships with the local schools that know the kids who are in need and help reach out to each parent. Many people from the community also volunteer to support the operations of the summer meal program. Read more about how Fish Community Food Bank has blossomed thanks to summer meal programs at the link in bio! #EndSummerHunger

Dr. Gwendolyne Jack remembers meeting Dr. Erica Phillips about seven years ago, not long after Dr. Jack joined #NYPWeillCornell. Dr. Jack, an endocrinologist, had a degree in public health and wanted to continue working to improve the health of communities. Dr. Phillips, who has spent more than two decades as an internist and health services researcher, was happy to provide mentorship.

“I have these grand visions and dreams, and Dr. Phillips told me to ‘dream big, but start small’,” says Dr. Jack.

“The most important thing for me about mentorship is learning how to get out of the way of your mentees and allow them to lead,” says Dr. Phillips.

The two physicians now talk several times a month, and Dr. Jack recently took over a faculty development program Dr. Phillips launched five years ago. To mark Black History Month, they sat down together for a conversation with Health Matters about mentors, carrying on a legacy, and their commitment to helping the next generation. Tap the link in bio.

As an active 34-year-old, Jay G. never imagined he’d face heart failure. So, after he began experiencing chest pain, he was stunned to receive a diagnosis of an aortic aneurysm. He turned to NewYork-Presbyterian, where his care team created a plan to restore his heart function. 

After a successful surgery to replace his aortic root, Jay is embracing a new adventure—fatherhood. “I wouldn’t be here today with my new daughter without NewYork-Presbyterian,” he said. Having learned his condition is hereditary, Jay takes comfort in knowing his family can rely on #NYP. “Now we have care for my daughter in case she ever needs it.” 

More people trust their hearts to us than any other top hospital in the nation. Tap the link in our bio to learn more about our world-class cardiac care.

That “cheat meal” might sound good but it could be setting you up for failure. Life is short and food is meant to be enjoyed without guilt or the need to cheat. I help my clients build eating plans that include the foods they love so they don’t have to cheat. #FeedingTimeIsMyFavoriteTime
Sometimes we need to let go in order to move forward.

If you're struggling to follow a diet or to reduce your calorie intake in service of a desire to lose weight, it may mean that there is some work that you need to do before embarking on a weight loss journey that will help you be more successful. Often, we need to allocate time and energy to making adaptive changes so we can be successful with the technical changes. Don't keep shooting yourself in the foot. The One Step approach will help set you up for the long-term success you're looking for.

If you're eating something delicious and not enjoying every single bite and not saying to yourself, "That is so f*%king delicious", then you're not doing it right. Enjoying delicious goodies should be part of your plan. Let me show you how to eat what you love and love how you look and feel.
We’re in the business of cultivating confidence, autonomy, empowerment and peace of mind.

Our goal at One Step Nutrition Coaching is to give you the tools you need to be successful for long term. That starts with creating a strong foundation. Contact us today for your free consultation and let’s talk about how we can help you make your goals a reality.

Why we avoid citrus in skincare (even though we love it in our food… especially cake!) 🍊
Citrus—often praised for its fresh scent and vitamin C content—can actually cause more harm than good when applied to the skin. 😬

From hyperpigmentation and rashes to melasma and dermatitis, the photosensitive oils found in orange, grapefruit, and lemon can make your skin more prone to irritation, especially when exposed to sunlight.

We’ve seen these side effects firsthand—and even experienced them ourselves. That’s why we avoid citrus in all of our leave-on formulas. Instead, we use botanicals that nurture without the risk. 🌿

Citrus is great for boosting immunity and collagen when eaten, but when it comes to skincare, we’d rather skip the flare-ups and stick to gentle, skin-loving ingredients that won’t leave us with dark spots or irritation. ✨

#CitrusFree #SkinCare #NaturalBeauty

This piece is new and titled “I Met My Solitude” after the poem by Naomi Replanksy.

It starts: “I met my solitude. We stood glaring. I had to tremble, meeting her face to face. 
Then she saying, and I with bent head hearing: “You sent me forth to exile and disgrace.”
Most faithful of your friends, then most foresaken…”

Did you know you can have a delicious mac and cheese that’s packed with protein just by adding eggs and Stonyfield Organic Greek yogurt? Stonyfield Organic Greek yogurt is made with high-quality ingredients and adds a tangy kick that perfectly balances the cheese and creates a super creamy, comforting sauce! 🙌 Full recipe by @feelgoodfoodie below 👇 Let us know if you give this one a try!

INGREDIENTS:

1 pound elbow macaroni
2 cups 2% milk
1 cup Stonyfield whole milk Greek yogurt
2 tablespoons unsalted butter
2 teaspoons salt
½ teaspoon black pepper
½ teaspoon mustard powder
½ teaspoon paprika
2 cups shredded sharp cheddar cheese
4 eggs

INSTRUCTIONS:

1. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook the pasta al dente according to package instructions. Reserve 1 cup of the cooking water, drain and set aside.

2. Heat the same pot used for the pasta over medium-low heat. Add the milk, Greek yogurt, butter, salt, pepper, mustard and paprika. Whisk together until combined and heated through, about 5 minutes.

3. Add the cooked pasta and ½ cup of the reserved pasta water, and toss to fully coat for about 2 minutes.

4. In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs and cheese until they form a paste.

5. Turn off the heat and stir in the cheese until melted completely. Add more pasta water to adjust if needed, and serve immediately.

Roughly 200,000 miles of Duke Energy above-ground power lines wind through a six-state footprint that includes the highlands of Kentucky, the mountains of western North Carolina, and the towering willow oaks of Charlotte. In each of these areas, trees and vegetation can pose hazards to power lines and thus, reliability.

Because of the varied terrain Duke Energy covers, the company employs two vegetation teams and a variety of pruning tools and methods to clear trees and vegetation that may interfere with the lines.

“The objective is to maintain the lines – before the trees and brush are close enough to cause outages – in a manner that is consistent with good arboricultural practices,” said Wesley Frick, manager of distribution vegetation at Duke Energy.

Click the link in our bio for more about the team responsible for vegetation management.

“On high-energy demand days – like those we saw in January – Lincoln 17 performed efficiently.”

Lincoln 17 — the new 402-megawatt simple-cycle combustion turbine generator, built at the existing Lincoln Combustion Turbine Station near Denver, N.C. — is the most efficient natural gas turbine in our fleet. The gas turbine provides the replacement generation needed to retire the last two units at Allen Steam Station. 

Lincoln 17 can reach full power in roughly 10 minutes – faster than any other turbine of its kind. This flexibility is essential on cold winter mornings or hot summer afternoons, when customers use a lot of electricity.

Dubai chocolate inspired stuffed dates. 

Ingredients: 
8–10 Dates
1 cup of chocolate chips or chocolate bar of choice
200g of Pistachio Kataifi: see recipe below 

Separate each date a little and add 1–2 teaspoons of pistachio kanafi to each date. After all the dates are stuffed, put them in the fridge for a few minutes.  In a microwave-safe bowl, add 1 cup of chocolate chips and a teaspoon of coconut oil and melt in the microwave in 20-second increments till smooth.  Take your dates out of the fridge and dip each one in the melted chocolate and lay them out onto a plate lined with parchment paper.  Sprinkle with chopped pistachios. Transfer back to the fridge for the chocolate to fully set.  Enjoy! 

Pistachio Kataifi recipe: 
Melt 4 tablespoons of butter in a pan, add 200g of Kataifi and toast till golden brown. Remove from heat and add about 2 tablespoons of pistachio cream and mix well.

Hamza Igamane is a cult hero. The Old Firm derby has a soft spot for producing classic moments, and this one is due to go platinum. Came off the bench in the 83rd minute. Bagged the winner just five minutes later. Real hitman settings. Secured Rangers’ first league win at Celtic Park in four years. The Moroccan Morelos is mashing work. You’re looking at a proper bagsman who can rise to the occasion and rise it when it truly matters. Pulled up to the opp block and got to chopping. Call this baller the couscous McCoist the way he led Celtic fans down a blind Ally. But let’s talk about that finish. Minimal backlift, but the power could’ve moved the Atlas Mountains. A winner so cold, it had Václav Černý spraying his drink on the home fans like Steve Austin. Igamane is HIM.

Big Dan Burn is every Newcastle United fan. Word to Sampha, sometimes you have to let it all work out. From son of the soil, to blossoming at the home of football. Dreams really do come true. BDB saw the Wembley arch and rose to the occasion. The club’s first goal at the home of English football for 25 years. The club’s first trophy delivered for over 70 years. Had Mac Allister defending corner kicks like Rey Mysterio squaring up to the Great Khali. While this green giant had corn for Liverpool, don’t forget how he had to get it out the mud. Went from being released by his boyhood club, to releasing them from the shackles of not seeing silverware. Navigated the choppy seas of non-league football only to steer the ship to the promised land of success. From local lad, to Local Hero. The boy from Blyth proved he’s a Spartan. Not only did he do it for himself. He put on for the city. Don’t get his antics mixed up with the joy of celebrating a goal. He had the spirit of 32,000 fans living vicariously through him. You can face setbacks. You can face adversity. But if you stay the course, the moment will arrive that makes it all worth it. Howay the lads.

A new research study by the Professional Footballers’ Association (PFA) is investigating the prevalence of neurodiversity in current footballers in England.⁣
⁣
Neurodiversity is yet to be extensively researched in the professional game. The PFA’s study is the first of its kind in professional football and seeks to help establish a better understanding of neurodivergent experiences at the elite level.⁣
⁣
700 players have been surveyed so far, and preliminary findings show only 5% of participants have been formally diagnosed with a neurodiverse condition. Among the most commonly self-reported neurodiverse traits are difficulties with attention and focus (26%) and social interactions (22%).⁣
⁣
The union’s study began in October 2024 and is expected to be completed by the end of the 2024/25 season. The results will then be shared to aid the development of more inclusive practices for clubs to implement.⁣
⁣
Manchester United’s Safia Middleton-Patel has been diagnosed autistic and says this research study can improve understanding and awareness of neurodiversity in football.⁣
⁣
“I wish it was something I had when I was younger.” Middleton-Patel said. “It’s really good for the players to help understand themselves more, but it will be very beneficial for clubs to find structures where they can adapt training or meetings to suit the players’ needs.”⁣
⁣
This study has been a long time coming. Several current and former players with neurodiverse conditions have spoken about their experiences of playing professionally, and some have rightly called for more to be done to raise awareness of neurodiversity in football.⁣
⁣
This research could be the progress the sport has needed.

adidas made waves on the pitch with the return of the Predator, and now they’re doing the same off it with the long-awaited release of the Predator Megaride.

After rumours emerged late last year, the Three Stripes have officially tied the knot between the Predator and iconic running sneaker, releasing a blacked-out model that will have the streets for years to come.

Arriving in all black, the release turns heads the same way both models did in ‘06. A combination of classic elements transforms a look of the past into the present, all while staying close to their roots.

Like previous Megaride models, the sneakers feature a bounce-tractioned footbed, maximising comfort with every step. As for the aesthetic, the Absolute-inspired look takes control, featuring everything from the fold-over tongue and strike zone right the way to the embossed ‘Teamgeist’ logo on the heel.

The adidas Predator Megaride is available now via END and select retailers.

adidas and Germany are celebrating 125 years of the national team with a special-edition jersey.

The anniversary kit is a blast from the past, with the duo unlocking a time capsule to release a retro beauty. Designed in a similar style to the kits Germany wore in the late ‘60s and ‘70s, the shirt arrives in a simple ivory base with a black collar and sleeve cuffs.

Instead of the modern crest that has adorned DFB jerseys for decades now, the kit is embroidered with the federation’s original design from 1900. Updating it for the milestone year, a commemorative ‘125’ is stitched onto the circular badge.

A subtle, jacquard eagle design is woven behind the crest – the perfect finishing touch to an understated masterpiece.

The goalkeeper kit takes on the same design, with the only difference being a baby blue base that nods to the signature colourway Germany’s No. 1 wore in decades past.

The 125th anniversary kit is available to purchase now on the adidas website and select retailers.

🎉 Happy Cancerversary to Julie, Founder of Wellnest! 🎉

“Two years ago, I was diagnosed with triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC), a moment that changed everything. Through 28 rounds of chemo, 14 rounds of immunotherapy, surgery, and 15 sessions of radiation, I not only fought for my own healing but also built a platform to support others navigating medical hardships. 💚

Today, I’m celebrating resilience, the power of community, and the incredible support network that has carried me through this journey. Wellnest was born from the belief that no one should have to go through hard times alone—and I’m so grateful for everyone who has been part of my story.”

Celebrating a Big Win for the Planet!
We are overjoyed to share the success of our “Plastic Mukt Shala” campaign, a heartwarming collaboration between Dost Foundation and Dabur India Limited to conduct a mega plastic waste collection drive in government schools in Kheda District of Gujarat. This incredible initiative saw 51,000 enthusiastic students come together to collect and submit an astounding 1,51,000 plastic bottles for recycling! ♻️
These young eco-warriors gathered plastic waste from their schools and surrounding villages. Their dedication and hard work have made a significant impact on the environment, setting a shining example for us all. 🌍✨
This unique campaign has been recognized and certified by the Worldwide Books of Records. A big shoutout to the Dost Foundation team and Dabur family for making this happen. 🏆👏
Let’s continue to work hand in hand towards a cleaner, greener future! 🌱💚

Spring has sprung with this adorable treat 🌼

Ingredients:
1 Box JELL-O Chocolate Pudding
Chocolate Cookies
Jet-Puffed Marshmallows
Chocolate Candies

How to Make It:
1. Prepare JELL-O according to the instructions on package. Crush chocolate cookies.
2. In a cup, layer JELL-O pudding and crushed cookies.
3. Cut a Jet-Puffed Marshmallow into thin pieces. Arrange in the shape of a flower, with the chocolate candy as the center. Place atop your JELL-O pudding cup and enjoy!
